The paper deals with the detection of Return-oriented programming (ROP) attacks using deep neural networks. This topic falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also involves the use of machine learning techniques, specifically deep neural networks, which could potentially place it under the categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper involves the testing of the proposed method against various types of ROP exploits, which could place it under the categories of software engineering (cs.SE) and systems and control (cs.SI).
